name: Apartment 7A
summary: "Apartment 7A" has garnered varied reviews, with some praising its premise as a prequel to "Rosemary's Baby" and others criticizing it for lacking originality. The New York Times notes that while the film has "all devil," it is short on details. IGN finds it has "mild chills" but also "chilling relevancy," while The Guardian deems it a "vacant rehash." Town & Country explores the film's connection to the Dakota building, which it asks if it is haunted. The Daily Beast declares it "the most pointless prequel ever," while Mashable praises Julia Garner's performance in a "suitably savage" prequel. The Hollywood Reporter provides details on how to watch the film online. TheWrap labels it a "paint-by-numbers" prequel, and Screen Rant analyzes its mid-credits scene, explaining its significance for "Rosemary's Baby."

name: Washington football
summary: The University of Washington Huskies will face the Rutgers Scarlet Knights in their first away game of the 2024 season. The game will be broadcast on Metro Sports TV at 7:30 PM. Despite the anticipated matchup, Washington football fans expressed frustration with their team's poor performance in the first half against Rutgers. Live coverage, including scores and highlights, will be available on various platforms such as PennLive, Rutgers Scarlet Knights, and Asbury Park Press. The distance between Washington and Rutgers for the game is a significant 2,400 miles, which will affect travel time and logistics. Live updates and scores will also be provided by the Yakima Herald-Republic. In a surprising turn of events, Grady Gross missed a game-tying field goal, resulting in Washington's loss to Rutgers on the road. Additionally, it has been reported that Parham has quit the Huskies on the eve of the Rutgers game, raising questions about the team's morale and cohesion.

name: Will and Harper
summary: The latest news surrounding Will Ferrell centers around his new film, "Will & Harper," which explores the topic of transgenderism. In an interview with The Independent, Ferrell expresses his support for transgender people and questions the reasons for any perceived threat they may pose. The Washington Post highlights the film's innovative humor, while the Fort Worth Report focuses on its depiction of a road trip conversation between two friends, one of whom is transgender. Several articles, including Vulture, Xtra Magazine, and Roger Ebert, emphasize the importance of allyship and the need for non-transgender individuals to support and understand transgender people. "Will & Harper" is also being compared to the popular sitcom "Will & Grace," with the Los Angeles Times describing it as the transgender version of the show. The Ankler's podcast interview with Ferrell and Harper Steele, a transgender activist, further delves into the film's themes of friendship and acceptance.

name: North Carolina governor Mark Robinson
summary: Mark Robinson's gubernatorial campaign in North Carolina has faced significant challenges. Despite suffering a hand injury at an event, Robinson resumed campaigning on Saturday. Half of his state staff has resigned, following an earlier exodus of campaign staff. The controversy stems from a report alleging racist comments by Robinson, sparking a historic potential defeat. Remaining staff has quit after a porn website scandal, and neighboring states' governors have abandoned his campaign. Robinson, the GOP nominee, has attempted to suppress dissent within the party, raising questions about its impact on Donald Trump's presidential chances.

Democrats hope to make electoral gains in North Carolina, while Trump's rally sparked controversy over his gubernatorial candidate.

summary: In preparation for Hurricane Helene's landfall, FEMA is establishing an incident support base at Maxwell-Gunter Air Force Base. The federal government is investing in community resilience through a collaboration between the NFL and FEMA, which will make designated venues available during disasters. Despite efforts towards disaster preparedness, FEMA's bureaucratic processes have led to financial burdens for Vermont towns during recovery.

name: Unicoi County
summary: Recent flooding caused by Hurricane Helene led to a dramatic rescue operation at Unicoi County Hospital in Tennessee. Over 50 individuals, including patients and staff, were stranded on the hospital's roof as water levels rose rapidly. The Tennessee National Guard, Tennessee Highway Patrol, and Knox County Sheriff's Office deployed helicopters to evacuate all those in need, with the assistance of medical personnel and police officers. The rescue was described as "dangerous" due to the treacherous conditions, but all the stranded individuals were successfully rescued.

summary: ABC's new medical drama, "Doctor Odyssey," follows Dr. Max Bankman, played by Joshua Jackson, as he embarks on a journey as a doctor on a luxury cruise ship. Despite being hailed as a "modern twist" on traditional network shows, critics note its surface-level approach and reliance on a "sexy network TV" aesthetic. The show has generated buzz for its star power and escapist premise, with some viewers finding it enjoyable as a lighthearted adventure. However, others have criticized it for its lack of depth and formulaic storytelling. Regardless of the mixed reviews, the show is available for free streaming through various platforms, making it accessible to a wide audience.

name: Power outage
summary: Hurricane Helene has caused widespread power outages across several southeastern states, with over 1 million outages reported in South and North Carolina alone. Howard University students are calling for accommodations after a power outage disrupted air conditioning and hot water in their dorms. Panama City and Bay County in Florida have also been impacted, with a power outage map available to track the outages. Indiana residents can check their status with power outage maps provided by IndyStar. Central Florida is also tracking power outages as Helene nears. Tallahassee and Leon County in Florida have released a power outage map as well. Duke Energy has reported that nearly 198,000 customers have had their power restored following Hurricane Helene's landfall. Additionally, hundreds of customers along Chatham Parkway in Georgia are experiencing a power outage. In Ecuador, widespread power outages have been reported, leading to 12-hour power cuts and multiple deaths due to Tropical Storm Helene.
